`` Vigorous monitoring and enforcement of trade agreements is a top priority of this administration , '' U.S. Trade Representative Charlene Barshefsky said in a statement .
Another senior U.S. trade official said Washington could launch WTO complaints later this year if governments refused to reform .
The annual report assesses U.S. commercial relations with 54 major trading partners and highlights policies the United States said unfairly restricted trade in goods and services .
In contrast to a critical assessment in 1999 , China was praised for progress on reforms .
The report said the Clinton administration 's trade pact with China would provide U.S. companies unprecedented access to the vast Chinese market .
